Home Automation Using NodeMCU & Blynk
Problem Statement:
Manual control of home appliances is inconvenient and lacks
remote access functionality.
Objective:
Create a home automation system using NodeMCU and Blynk to
control appliances like lights and fans remotely.
Requirements:
NodeMCU ESP8266
2-Channel or 4-Channel Relay Module
LED bulbs (or simulate with LEDs)
Blynk App (Android/iOS)
Jumper wires, breadboard
Power supply
Expected Outcome:
A fully functional remote-controlled system that switches
appliances ON/OFF via smartphone.

